#: src/deployment/csr.md:536
msgid "Netlify"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:538
msgid ""
"All it takes to deploy a Leptos CSR app to Netlify is to create a project "
"and to add two simple configuration files in your project root. Let's begin "
"with the latter."
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:542
msgid "Configuration Files"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:544
msgid ""
"Create a `netlify.toml` file in your project root with the following content:"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:546
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[build]\n"
"command = \"rustup target add wasm32-unknown-unknown && cargo install trunk "
"--locked && trunk build --release\"\n"
"publish = \"dist\"\n"
"\n"
"[build.environment]\n"
"RUST_VERSION = \"stable\"\n"
"\n"
"[[redirects]]\n"
"from = \"/*\"\n"
"to = \"/index.html\"\n"
"status = 200\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:560
msgid ""
"Create a `rust-toolchain.toml` file in your project root with the following "
"content:"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:563
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[toolchain]\n"
"channel = \"stable\"\n"
"targets = [\"wasm32-unknown-unknown\"]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:569
msgid "Deployment"
msgstr "部署"

#: src/deployment/csr.md:571
msgid ""
"[Add your project to Netlify](https://docs.netlify.com/start/add-new-"
"project/) by connecting your Git repository"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:573
msgid "Netlify will automatically detect your `netlify.toml` configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:574
msgid ""
"If you need additional environment variables, configure them in [Netlify's "
"environment variables settings](https://docs.netlify.com/build/environment-"
"variables/overview/)"
msgstr ""

#: src/deployment/csr.md:577
msgid ""
"The `rust-toolchain.toml` ensures the correct Rust toolchain and WASM target "
"are available during the build process. The redirect rule in `netlify.toml` "
"ensures your SPA routes work correctly by serving `index.html` for all paths."
msgstr ""
